  {
    "id": 17,
    "title": "Stephaniviertel",
    "contact_information": "Taxistand Radio Bremen",
    "content": "Employees of Radio Bremen and Radio Bremen's subsidiary company Bremedia have come together in a strike to address significant differences in wages and working conditions. The strike is supported by Labor unions like e.g. IG Metall or VERDI, but also political representatives. We were there and could listen to a speech, strike represantatives held to highlight the main Points of the strike.\r\n\r\nOne core issue discussed in the strike speech was the wage difference between employees at Radio Bremen and those at Bremedia. While having similar work tasks, the employees of Bremedia are paid significantly less - an example difference of 2500€ was named. Next negotiations will focus narrowing this gap.\r\nOther issues talked About were Inflation Adjustments, since the Inflation rate reaches 10%, though the proposed wage increase of 4.71% and additionally 1.23% over two years seem insufficient.\r\nThey also talked about Freelance workers facing unfair conditions like conditionally less wage when being sick or a lack of compensation for maternity leave for those working at multiple institutions of the ARD.\r\nLastly, they mentioned employees working during \"unsocial\" hours, who should be compensated properly when working night shifts, weekends, or puplic holidays. \r\n\r\nDuring the time of the strike the People of Bremen could have noticed the strike. To make the strike's issues more public, disruptions in the regular programm were initiated: propular programs like Buten und Binnen, weather or sports programs have been canceled or replaced last minute by Content from other ARD institutions. These Actions should have raised public attention. \r\n\r\nWith more negotiations to come, employees of both Radio Bremen and Bremedia have made it clear to continue their effords to fight for more fairness, equity, and recognition for their issues.",
    "citations": "Cay, B. (2024). Taxistand Radio Bremen strike on Hinter d. Mauer. V1. [Dataset SmartBremen 28195].\r\nGonsal, L. (2024). Taxistand Radio Bremen strike on Hinter d. Mauer. V1. [Dataset SmartBremen 28195].",
