  {
    "id": 18,
    "title": "Stephaniviertel",
    "contact_information": "https://www.inneremission-bremen.de/",
    "content": "The facade of Innere Mission Bremen is a vibrant mosaic of color and creativity, blending bold shapes with bright, sunny hues. Designed through a collaboration between government and students from the University of the Arts Bremen (HfK), this piece transforms the building into a visual celebration of art and community. The cheerful design not only enlivens the street but also reflects the organization’s mission of hope and support within Bremen. To read more about their mission and role in community: https://www.inneremission-bremen.de/",
    "citations": "Cay, B. (2024). Women's shelter on Abbentorstraße. V1. [Dataset SmartBremen 28195].",
